<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06182204 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06182204 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  SAN-JOSE; MAN; AUTO; DEATH; POLICE; ESCAPE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A San Jose man was killed early Saturday when he crashed on Monterey Roadafter eluding police in a chase that reached speeds of 100 mph.;    JoeCaudillo Jr., 36, was ejected from his car in front of the Oasis Motel inSouth San Jose and was pronounced dead at the scene by paramedics.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  POLICE CHASE ENDS IN DEATH  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The pursuit began at 2:43 a.m. in Morgan Hill after Caudillo refused tostop for police who spotted his car moving erratically and at a high rate ofspeed in the northbound lanes of Monterey Road.;    Morgan Hill officers brokeoff the chase at Bernal Road. San Jose police units were called forassistance, but Caudillo crashed before they arrived.;    Caudillo's vehiclestruck two traffic lights, a utility pole and a sign at the motel.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Staff Report  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910630  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  129  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday June 30, 199100182204,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>